{
  "doc_id": "51723",
  "text": "Given that hippocampus is associated with detailed memory for context [CITATION_1] whereas amygdala is associated with emotional information [CITATION_2] and memory 'gist' [CITATION_3] , these findings also suggest that males and females show biases in retrieval of affective and contextual information. This possibility parallels findings from spatial memory tasks where sex differences are reliably observed in the kind of information and strategies preferentially used [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] . Whether males and females similarly show different dominant strategies for context fear conditioning remains unknown.",
